main event: A UFO sighting report was gathered at National City Airport, California on May 23-24, 1958.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 10 minutes,The object was observed making circular maneuvers,The possibility of the object being a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical event was suggested,No size or cloud cover details were provided to assist with evaluation,One confirmed witness was associated with the report.
witness description: Civilian patrolman Leonard E. Wade, age 23, and a 21-year-old employed by the Crawford Detective Agency.
